97
00:05:04,705 --> 00:05:06,320
If we print the result of that,

98
00:05:06,320 --> 00:05:10,530
we can see many missing values in different columns of the dataset like body,

99
00:05:10,530 --> 00:05:12,560
cabin, boat, age, embarked, etc.

100
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:15,860
Let's focus on the age and body columns and look at how to impute

101
00:05:15,860 --> 00:05:20,230
these values for numerical variables using an sklearn solution, simple imputer.

102
00:05:20,230 --> 00:05:22,910
Here we create an instance of the simple imputer class.

103
00:05:22,910 --> 00:05:28,265
We define the missing value placeholders as np.nans and set the strategy to mean,

104
00:05:28,265 --> 00:05:32,035
which means we want to replace the missing values with the mean value of the column.

105
00:05:32,035 --> 00:05:35,300
Then we apply it to the age and body columns of

106
00:05:35,300 --> 00:05:38,795
the x_test DataFrame using the fit transform method,

107
00:05:38,795 --> 00:05:43,205
where we're fitting and transforming all in one and store the result in simple imputed.

108
00:05:43,205 --> 00:05:46,190
Next what I'm going to do to make it easier for us to look at this,

